Download glibc source code from http://ftp.gnu.org/gnu/glibc/
uncompress the targeted version into your home directory

create a standlone directory, for exemple glibc
go into this directory

then type :
$ export CFLAGS='-g -O2 -fno-stack-protector'
$ ~/glibc-[version]/configure --prefix=/

the file that interrest us is : elf/ld.so
